Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration. 4f3f2ad7-8df5-4029-b249-1564571c14b0.14154404-6280-472d-ac61-75a900f4270d.prompt=Acceptable average latency threshold\: 4f3f2ad7-8df5-4029-b249-1564571c14b0.155144ea-41cc-4914-a596-1eeafeca1d11.description=Allows a user to select how they should be notified of the outcome of a flow, and shows them a message in that way. Responses\: success - The user was notified. failure - Notification failed. 4f3f2ad7-8df5-4029-b249-1564571c14b0.155144ea-41cc-4914-a596-1eeafeca1d11.prompt=Here is your diagnostic for ${host} 4f3f2ad7-8df5-4029-b249-1564571c14b0.238e0c76-32a0-4c10-8da2-65c668e8f7e3.prompt=Password\: 4f3f2ad7-8df5-4029-b249-1564571c14b0.28afae74-e78d-466f-8e8d-b95bc1dc9497.prompt=Server Name - The name of the server to test the connection to. 4f3f2ad7-8df5-4029-b249-1564571c14b0.319ff257-37cd-461e-b8bd-cc5eae815f0c.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

Inputs\:

4f3f2ad7-8df5-4029-b249-1564571c14b0.9409ba9e-744f-4c0b-8e41-2417e9f1d79c.description=
Performs a statistical operation on the given table's columns.

Inputs\:
table                  - The tale to analyze.
rowDelimiter      - A delimiter that separates rows in the table.
columnDelimiter - A delimiter that separates columns in the table.
header              - A columnDelimiter separated list of The names of columns.
rowNames         - The name of each row of data.

Returns\:
An html formatted statistical analysis of the table.

ExtraResults\:
means    - A columnDelimiter separated list of the column means.
medians  - A columnDelimiter separated list of the column medians.
stddevs  - A columnDelimiter separated list of the column standard deviations.
zValues   - A columnDelimiter separated list of the column z values.

Responses\:
success - the operation completed successfully.
failure - failed to process the list or something went wrong.
4f3f2ad7-8df5-4029-b249-1564571c14b0.95b52484-0a94-4851-90c4-225cf9644861.prompt=Protocol\: 4f3f2ad7-8df5-4029-b249-1564571c14b0.9683702a-b872-49bc-96f2-0f93239c3c5f.prompt=Hosts to perform test from (comma delimiter) 4f3f2ad7-8df5-4029-b249-1564571c14b0.9e6890e8-3051-4838-8a89-798cd3458e08.description=Check to see if the value stored in a specified key is null. Inputs\: keyName - the key to check Responses\: isNull - if the key is a null pointer. notNull - if some value is stored in the key. 4f3f2ad7-8df5-4029-b249-1564571c14b0.a09d579c-85db-4c70-bdb6-cc4567948ec8.prompt=Notification method\: 4f3f2ad7-8df5-4029-b249-1564571c14b0.bd2ed52e-dccd-4148-a685-0c9b606533e7.description=
 Detects the operating system that is running on the specified host.

Inputs\:
    host - The host to connect to.
    username - The username to use when connecting.
    password - The password to use when connecting.

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. The name and the version of the operating system.
    osName - The completely returned string of the OS name.
    version - The operating systems version.
    hostName - The host name the remote computer reports for itself.
    enterprise - 'true' if the operating system is an enterprise edition
    server - 'true' if the operating system is a server edition
    professional - 'true' if the operating system is a professional edition.
    standard - 'true' if the operating system is a standard edition.

Responses\:
    windows - Remote host is running a version of windows.
    linux - Remote host is running linux.
    solaris - Remote host is running solaris.
    other unix - Remote host appears to be unix based, but is an unknown variant.
    failure - System could not determine remote hosts operating system.

Notes\:
1. The enterprise, server, professional and standard results give more details about what version of windows is detected and are always set to 'false' if a unix system is being run.
2. The operation returns the output of a uname -a for unix based hosts, and the results of osName and version WMI queries for a windows host.

Checks to see whether or not a connection exists, and if it exists checks to see if it is adequately reliable. Diagnoses what is wrong with the connection from multiple hosts..

Inputs\:
target - The host to ping.
hosts - A comma separated list of the hosts to ping from.
username - Username for hosts.
password - Password for hosts.
delimiter - The delimiter for hosts.
lossThreshold - What percentage of packet loss you consider to be acceptable for this connection.
latencyThreshold - How long (in milliseconds) you consider to be an acceptable latency for this connection.
diagnostic so far - The result of previous diagnosis, used for chaining.
maxhops - How many hops traceroute diagnostic will descend.
notifyMethod - How to report the diagnostic.

Responses\:
success - No problems found.
diagnosed - Problems found.
failure - Something went wrong.

Recommended Thresholds\:
Connection Type		Loss Threshold (%)	Latency Threshold (ms)
DSL modem			2		200
Cable modem		2		200
Dialup modem		2		500
ISDN Line			2		150
T1/T3/OCR			2		80
10 ethernet			2		10
Wireless			2		600
